<sect1 id="file-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>File</guimenu> Menu</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="filenew.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>New Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Allows you to create a new &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>O</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Open</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="fileopen.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Open Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Opens an existing &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Open Recent</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Opens a recently used &krayon; image. A submenu will open
displaying recent &krayon; images that you have used.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="filesave.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Save Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Saves the current &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Save As...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Saves the &krayon; image under a new name.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>P</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Print...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="fileprint.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Print Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Prints the current &krayon; image. This will open the
<guilabel>Setup Printer</guilabel> dialog, to set the printing
parameters and print the image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Document Information...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="documentinfo.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Info Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>This opens the <guilabel>Document Information</guilabel>
dialog. This lets you enter information about current &krayon;
image. This information will be saved with the image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Close</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="fileclose.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Close Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Closes the current &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut>
<keycombo action="simul">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="exit.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Quit Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>>Quits &krayon;. This will only quit the current &krayon;
window if more than one is open.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="edit-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> Menu</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Cut</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="editcut.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Cut Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Removes the selection from the image and places it in the
clipboard.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>X</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Copy</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="editcopy.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Copy Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Copies the selection to the clipboard. This is different from the
<guimenuitem>Cut</guimenuitem> in that it does not remove the
selection from the image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>V</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Paste</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="editpaste.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Paste Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Inserts the selection from the clipboard into the image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Crop</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Crops the &krayon; image to the selection. The image will be
resized to the size of the selection rectangle, and all parts of
the image outside of the selection rectangle will be removed.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<shortcut><keycombo action="simul">
&Ctrl;<keycap>A</keycap>
</keycombo></shortcut>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Select All</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>TODO: How will this work on an image? Find out...</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Unselect All</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Removes all selections from the image. This is the opposite
of <guimenuitem>Select All</guimenuitem></para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="view-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>View</guimenu> Menu</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>New View</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Open up a new view window for the current &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Close All Views</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Close all open view windows.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Split View</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Split the current view into two. This does not open a
separate &krayon; window, but splits the current window into two.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Remove View</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Closes the current &krayon; split view.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Splitter Orientation</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Change the orientation of the split views. You may choose to
split the view horizontally or vertically.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Zoom in</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="viewmag+.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Zoom In Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Zoom in on the current view. This <quote>magnifies</quote>
your view of the image, making it easier to work on image
details.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>View</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Zoom out</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="viewmag-.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Zoom Out Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Zoom out from the current view. This is the opposite of the
<guimenuitem>Zoom in</guimenuitem> command.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

