<sect1 id="tools-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>Tools</guimenu> Menu</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Rectangular select</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Rectangular select</guimenuitem>
tool. You use this tool to select rectangular regions of the
&krayon; image. These regions can then be copied, moved, or
removed.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Move tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Move</guimenuitem> tool. You use
this to move selected regions of the &krayon; image.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Zoom tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Zoom</guimenuitem> tool. You use
this to zoom in or out of the image view. Clicking with the left
mouse button magnifies the image while clicking with the right
mouse button demagnifies the image. These behave identical to the
<guimenuitem>Zoom in</guimenuitem> and <guimenuitem>Zoom
out</guimenuitem> commands on the<guimenuitem>View</guimenuitem>
menu.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Color picker</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Color picker</guimenuitem>
tool. You use this to select a color from a &krayon; image. Using
the <guimenuitem>Color picker</guimenuitem> is often easier than
editing the color values on the <guilabel>Sidebar</guilabel>.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Pen tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Pen</guimenuitem> tool. You use
this to draw basic lines on the &krayon; image. Lines drawn with
the <guimenuitem>Pen</guimenuitem> have sharp edges.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Brush tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Brush</guimenuitem> tool. You use
this to draw basic lines on the &krayon; image. Unlike the
<guimenuitem>Pen</guimenuitem> tool, the
<guimenuitem>Brush</guimenuitem> draws lines with
<quote>fuzzy</quote> edges.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Airbrush tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Airbrush</guimenuitem> tool. This
is similar to the <guimenuitem>Brush</guimenuitem> tool, but draws
lines in an airbrushed style.</para>
<!-- TODO: figure out exactly what Airbrush does. Is it pressure sensitive? -->
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Gradient tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Gradient</guimenuitem> tool. This
fills in areas of the &krayon; image with the currently selected
gradient.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Eraser tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Eraser</guimenuitem> tool. This removes
color from the image. It can be helpful to think of the
<guimenuitem>Eraser</guimenuitem> as a
<guimenuitem>Pen</guimenuitem> that draws in an
<quote>erasing</quote> color.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Tools</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Filler tool</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Chooses the <guimenuitem>Filler</guimenuitem> tool. This
fills in regions of the &krayon; image with a color or pattern.</para>
<!-- TODO: how to define fill boundary -->
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="image-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>Image</guimenu> Menu</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Import Image</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="wizard.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Import Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Import an image into &krayon;. Besides the default
<filename>KRA</filename> format, &krayon; can load images stored
in a variety of formats, including <filename>PNG</filename>,
<filename>XPM</filename>, <filename>BMP</filename>, and
<filename>JPEG</filename> formats.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Export Image</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
<guiicon>
<inlinemediaobject>
<imageobject>
<imagedata fileref="wizard.png" format="PNG"/>
</imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>Export Icon</phrase></textobject>
</inlinemediaobject>
</guiicon>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Export an image to another format. This saves the &krayon;
image to another image format. See the <guimenuitem>Import
Image</guimenuitem> paragraph above for the kinds of formats that
&krayon; recognizes.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Add new image tab</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>You can have more than one image open in &krayon; at a
time. By selecting this item, &krayon; creates a new image, and
adds a tab at the bottom of the image view. By selecting between
these tabs, you can switch between the different images.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Remove current image tab</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Removes the current image and image tab.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Merge all layers</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Merges all of the current image layers into a single
layer. This is useful if you have created multiple layers to work
on different parts of the image, and want to combine them all.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Merge all visible layers</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Merge all of the visible image layers into one. This is like
the <guimenuitem>Merge all layers</guimenuitem> command, but only
operates on the visible layers.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Image</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Merge all linked layers</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Merge all ofthe linked image layers into one. This is like
the <guimenuitem>Merge all layers</guimenuitem> command, but only
operates on the linked layers.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="layer-menu">
<title>The <guimenu>Layer</guimenu> Menu</title>
<para>TODO: should put general discussion of layers here, and
reference the concepts above.</para>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Insert layer...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Creates and inserts a new layer in the image. A useful way
to think of layers is to imagine them as sheets of glass stacked
atop each other. You can see through all the layers, but any
drawing you perform only changes the current layer. Some layers
are opaque and others are transparent.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Insert image as layer...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Inserts an image as a new layer. &krayon; will open an image
of any supported format and use it as a new drawing layer.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Save layer as standard image...</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>This command will save the current drawing layer as an image
file. Layers can be saved in any supported image format.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Rotate 90</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Rotates the current drawing layer 90 degrees clockwise.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Rotate 180</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Rotates the current drawing layer 180 degrees clockwise.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Rotate 270</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Rotates the current drawing layer 270 degrees clockwise.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Mirror X</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Mirrors the drawing layer about the X axis. This flips the
layer vertically.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>
<menuchoice>
<guimenu>Layer</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Mirror Y</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice>
</term>
<listitem>
<para>Mirrors the drawing layer about the Y axis. This flips the
layer horizontally.</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</sect1>

